IN preparing an Edition of a portion of the works of Tertullian for the Press, the first point to which my attention was naturally directed was the condition of the text.

Of the various Editions which have appeared of the works of this author and of the MSS. used by the Editors, there is a copious account in the last Paris Edition1 of Tertullian‚ published at¹ the Migne Press, in 1844, and in the recent Edition of Oehler 2.

The history of the Text is this.
